## Connectivity Between Servers

Ping is a common computer tool used to check whether your computer can communicate with another computer on a device or a network. I used ping to test the connectivity between my public instance server and my private instance server

The ping command I ran was ping 10.0.136.90

The first ping returned a single line. This meant that my Public Server has sent out a ping message... and that's about it.

